    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Helmet components, constituting that part which directly covers and protects the cranium; they occur in various shapes and may be made from either a single piece of metal or two overlapping halves joined at the comb.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000039541/Tarassuk and Blair, Complete Encyclopedia of Arms and Armor (1979)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Componentes del casco, constituyendo esa parte que cubre y protege directamente al cráneo; hay en varias formas y pueden ser hechos de una pieza única de metal o de dos mitades traslapadas unidas en el peine.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Onderdelen van een helm die de schedel precies bedekken en beschermen. Ze komen in vele vormen voor en kunnen uit één stuk metaal zijn vervaardigd of als twee overlappende helften, die bij de kam samenkomen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000052412/Wolters beeldwoordenboek (1986)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>頭盔組件中直接包裹保護顱骨的部分。有多種款式，有以單獨一片金屬製作成形的型式，也有以兩個半片交疊於頭冠處的型式。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Konstituierender Helmbestandteil, der den Schädel direkt bedeckt und schützt; er kommt in verschiedenen Formen vor und kann entweder aus einem einzigen Metallstück oder aus zwei sich überlappenden am Kamm verbundenen Hälften bestehen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
